items.title: Machine Learning with Ruby
items.content_text:
### Machine Learning Libraries / Vector search

*   [flann (‚≠ê2.3k)](https://github.com/mariusmuja/flann) -
    Ruby bindings for the [FLANN (‚≠ê2.3k)](https://github.com/flann-lib/flann) (Fast Library for Approximate Nearest Neighbors). <sup>\[[flann](#flann)]</sup>
*   [annoy-rb (‚≠ê36)](https://github.com/yoshoku/annoy.rb) -
    Ruby bindings for the [Annoy (‚≠ê14k)](https://github.com/spotify/annoy) (Approximate Nearest Neighbors Oh Yeah).
*   [hnswlib.rb (‚≠ê15)](https://github.com/yoshoku/hnswlib.rb) -
    Ruby bindings for the [Hnswlib (‚≠ê4.8k)](https://github.com/nmslib/hnswlib) that implements approximate nearest neighbor search with Hierarchical Navigable Small World graphs.
*   [ngt-ruby (‚≠ê53)](https://github.com/ankane/ngt-ruby) -
    Ruby bindings for the [NGT (‚≠ê1.3k)](https://github.com/yahoojapan/NGT) (Neighborhood Graph and Tree for Indexing High-dimensional data).
items.content_html:
Machine Learning Libraries / Vector search

  • flann (‚≠ê2.3k) - Ruby bindings for the FLANN (‚≠ê2.3k) (Fast Library for Approximate Nearest Neighbors). [flann]
  • annoy-rb (‚≠ê36) - Ruby bindings for the Annoy (‚≠ê14k) (Approximate Nearest Neighbors Oh Yeah).
  • hnswlib.rb (‚≠ê15) - Ruby bindings for the Hnswlib (‚≠ê4.8k) that implements approximate nearest neighbor search with Hierarchical Navigable Small World graphs.
  • ngt-ruby (‚≠ê53) - Ruby bindings for the NGT (‚≠ê1.3k) (Neighborhood Graph and Tree for Indexing High-dimensional data).

items.title: Awesome Transit
items.content_text:
### GTFS Libraries / Python

*   [gtfs-segments (‚≠ê43)](https://github.com/UTEL-UIUC/gtfs_segments) - Python package that represents GTFS data for buses in a concise tabular manner using segments.

### GTFS Analysis Tools / Rust

*   [GTFS Kit (‚≠ê81)](https://github.com/mrcagney/gtfs_kit) - A Python 3.6+ tool kit for analyzing General Transit Feed Specification (GTFS) data. Supersedes [GTFSTK](https://github.com/araichev/gtfstk).

### GTFS Timetable Publishing Tools / Rust

*   [GTFS-to-HTML](https://gtfstohtml.com) - Generate human-readable timetables in HTML or PDF format directly from GTFS.
*   [Timetable Kit (‚≠ê44)](https://github.com/neroden/timetable_kit) - An open source Python 3.10 module and scripts depending on [GTFS Kit (‚≠ê81)](https://github.com/mrcagney/gtfs_kit), designed to create complex printed/PDF timetables with flexible layouts. Currently only working out of the box for Amtrak's GTFS, but under active development.

items.title: Awesome Zsh Plugins
items.content_text:
### Plugins / [superconsole](https://github.com/alexchmykhalo/superconsole) - Windows-only

*   [autoupdate-oh-my-zsh-plugins (‚≠ê288)](https://github.com/TamCore/autoupdate-oh-my-zsh-plugins) - [oh-my-zsh](https://ohmyz.sh/) doesn't automatically update non-core plugins, this plugin autoupdates `git` repositories in the `$ZSH_CUSTOM` directory.
*   [coffee-time (‚≠ê2)](https://github.com/gakimball/zsh-coffee-time) - Adds the `caf` alias, which runs `caffeinate -dims`. The extra flags keep everything awake: the system, the drive, and the display.
*   [fast-alias-tips (‚≠ê14)](https://github.com/decayofmind/zsh-fast-alias-tips) - Helps remember the aliases you defined and forgot about. Ported from [djui/alias-tips (‚≠ê794)](https://github.com/djui/alias-tips). Active fork of [sei40kr/zsh-fast-alias-tips (‚≠ê60)](https://github.com/sei40kr/zsh-fast-alias-tips).
*   [gpt (‚≠ê20)](https://github.com/antonjs/zsh-gpt) - Enable querying ChatGPT from the command line.
*   [iterm2-shell-integration (‚≠ê59)](https://github.com/gnachman/iterm2-shell-integration) - Shell integration and utilities for iTerm2.
*   [macos-theme (‚≠ê0)](https://github.com/gakimball/zsh-macos-theme) - Adds the theme command, which toggles between light and dark mode in macOS. Requires [lux (‚≠ê35)](https://github.com/pndurette/zsh-lux) plugin.
*   [projen (‚≠ê0)](https://github.com/p6m7g8/p6-zsh-projen-plugin) - Adds aliases for [projen (‚≠ê2.8k)](https://github.com/projen/projen).
*   [show-git-user (‚≠ê5)](https://github.com/luisprgr/zsh-show-git-user) - When you need to work with multiple `git` users on the same machine this plugin will show which `git` user name is active in your prompt.

### Themes / [superconsole](https://github.com/alexchmykhalo/superconsole) - Windows-only

*   [zsh2000 (‚≠ê106)](https://github.com/consolemaverick/zsh2000) - Theme which resembles Powerline and includes the `rvm` prompt, `git` status and branch, current time, user, hostname, pwd, exit status, whether running as root and background job status.
